From Michael Covington Subject Re When are two people married in God's eyes In article A Robert Anderson writes I would like to get your opinions on this when exactly does an engaged couple become married in God's eyes Not if they are unwilling to go through a public marriage ceremony, nor if they say they are willing but have not actually done so Let's distinguish real logistical problems like being stranded on a desert island from excuses such as waiting for so and so's brother to come back from being in the army so he can be in the ceremony Michael A Covington, Associate Research Scientist Artificial Intelligence Programs The University of Georgia phone Athens, Georgia U S A amateur radio N TMI